  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally across five operating points to identify dominant geometric parameters driving hemolysis index variation; results confirmed that impeller tip clearance and rotational speed are primary drivers. This screening informs the factor assessments below but is captured only in narrative form.",
