      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH and RH index) directly maps to the clinical decision criterion and regulatory acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are the quantities used in the regulatory submission. Both are computed directly from CFD stress history integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks using the ASTM F1841 power-law model. The QoI chain from CFD output to regulatory criterion is unambiguous and documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
