      "rationale": "Simulation performed by analyst with 8 years CFD experience in cardiovascular applications. Peer review of simulation setup conducted by independent senior analyst. Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2 but qualitative controls in place."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published literature consensus for centrifugal pump hemolysis CFD. Newtonian blood analogue assumption valid at shear rates above 100 s⁻¹ prevalent in the pump. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients) is the regulatory standard. Formal model form uncertainty quantification deferred per MRL 2 scoping."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; nominal input values traceable to device specifications and literature.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from certified CMM measurements of production device. Fluid properties from published literature with traceability. Boundary conditions from device operating specifications. Input uncertainty propagation not formally quantified at MRL 2; a screening sensitivity study across the five operating points was performed narratively and confirmed that tip clearance and rotational speed are dominant drivers, supporting the adequacy of nominal inputs for the COU decision."
    },
